    },
    {
      "name": "groups",
      "description": "Operations about groups"
    },
    {
      "name": "me",
      "description": "Operations about mes"
    },
    {
      "name": "webhooks",
      "description": "These endpoints allow you to create and delete (unsubscribe from) webhooks.\n\n### Verifying webhook signatures\n\nWebhook payloads can be verified by calculating a signature for the payload\nyou receive, and comparing it to a signature provided in the request headers.\n\nTo verify the signature, you'll need:\n\n* the provided signature from the `x-participate-hmac-sha256` request header\n* the provided timestamp from the `x-participate-timestamp` request header\n* the raw request body (the payload)\n* the shared signing secret, which is the API key used to create the webhook\n\n_**Note:** When using multiple API keys to create webhooks, each webhook\nsignature must be verified with the same API key that created it. Track which\nAPI key corresponds to each webhook for proper verification._\n\nHere's an example of signature verification in Ruby:\n\n```ruby\nsecret = YOUR_API_KEY\npayload = request.body.read\ntimestamp = request.headers[\"x-participate-timestamp\"]\nprovided_signature = request.headers[\"x-participate-hmac-sha256\"]\n\ncalculated_signature =\n  OpenSSL::HMAC.hexdigest(\"SHA256\", secret, \"#{timestamp}#{payload}\")\n\nsignatures_match =\n  OpenSSL.fixed_length_secure_compare(\n    provided_signature,\n    calculated_signature\n  )\n\nif signatures_match\n  # the payload and timestamp have been verified so continue\n  # processing and confirm the timestamp is relatively recent\n  # to avoid replay attacks\n\n  grace_period = 60 # one minute\n  time_difference = (Time.now.to_i - timestamp.to_i).abs\n\n  if time_difference < grace_period\n    # the timestamp is close enough to the current time so\n    # continue and process the webhook payload\n\n    data = JSON.parse(payload)\n    do_something_with(data)\n  else\n    # there's an unacceptable time difference so abort processing\n  end\nelse\n  # signature verification has failed so abort processing\nend\n```\n"
    }
  ]
}